1. The Resurrection: “Death having been vanquished, Christ, the conqueror, returns from Limbo, and having broken the bonds of sin, He reopens the portals of heaven.'’

2. The Aseension: “Having appeared sufficiently long to men, He ascended into heaven and sits at the right hand of the Father‚ a oo-sharer of His glory.’'

3. The Cominy of the Holy Ghost: “The Holy Spirit whom He had already promised to His own, He showers down upon His sorrowing Apostles in fiery tongues of love.''

4. The Assumption of the Blessed Vir-gin.- “Liberated from the weight of the flesh, the Virgin is taken up to heaven; she is received with the jubilation of heaven, and with the songs of Angels.”
